\par\textbf{Citing the Bible by chapter and verse}

Unlike other books, we do not use page numbers to cite the Bible (page numbers vary from edition to edition and translation to translation).  We give the name of the book, then the chapter, then a colon, then verses.  Thus, we read “Deuteronomy 10:17-19” as “the book of Deuteronomy, chapter ten, verses seventeen through nineteen.” 
						\end{minipage}
