Church is always capitalized when it is part of a name of an organization, such as the Roman Catholic Church or the Presbyterian Church in America.  Theologians generally capitalize Church when they mean the one abstract ideal of the body of Christ, as in \textit{the} Church.  It is lowercase when it refers to any old church or churches, unless it is a title.  Thus, there are many Catholic churches in San Antonio, one of which is the church around the corner, the name of which is Holy Rosary Catholic Church. 
