\item \textbf{Matrimony} – Listening to many American Christians today you might think that \textbf{marriage} is the most sacred institution ever and the most important part of Christian life and teaching.  In fact, this was the last of the seven sacraments to be recognized by Catholicism.  Luther accepted the practice of matrimony, but did not recognize it as a sacrament instituted by Christ.  The only link between Jesus and matrimony is that Jesus went to a wedding when he was young.  The major discussion of matrimony in the New Testament is Paul discouraging it but permitting it as the lesser of the lust-based evils.  
